nodes.title: Final Prompt
widgets_values: The image shows a close-up of a keyboard with multiple keys. The keys are arranged in a grid-like pattern, with each key having a different color - white, red, blue, and black. The colors are vibrant and the keys appear to be glowing, giving the image a futuristic and technological feel. The background is black, making the colors of the keys stand out even more. The image is taken from a top-down perspective, looking down on the keys.

This was an experiment that just seems to work, I don't really know how or why. It seems that interpolation of latents with Flux yields more fine details in images. To vary an image more substantially you can try adding a node to set another seed for the 2nd pass, this allows you to change the image details while retaining quality and most of the composition. I haven't explored other types of styles with this workflow besides photos. I CANNOT PROVIDE SUPPORT FOR THIS, I'M JUST SHARING! 

This workflow uses araminta_k_flux_koda.safetensors which can be found at CivitAI. 
https://civitai.com/models/653093/Koda%20Diffusion%20(Flux) -- Amazing lora!  

The Flux.1 checkpoint used in this workflow is the dev version, if you're missing any custom nodes or get errors/red nodes please click manager and click on "Install Missing Custom Nodes", when the installation finishes click "Restart" as instructed, then reload the workflow.
  
I'm using an RTX 4090 with 24GB of RAM, each image takes approx. 98 seconds.
If you modify and share this workflow all I ask is that you credit me.
